38// If forced fallback is allowed, either:
39//
40// 1) The forced fallback is requested if the resolution is less than or equal
41// to |max_pixels_|. The resolution is allowed to be scaled down to
42// |min_pixels_|.
43//
44// 2) The forced fallback is requested if temporal support is preferred and the
45// SW fallback supports temporal layers while the HW encoder does not.
46
47struct ForcedFallbackParams {
48 public:
49 bool SupportsResolutionBasedSwitch(const VideoCodec& codec) const {
50 return enable_resolution_based_switch &&
51 codec.codecType == kVideoCodecVP8 &&
52 codec.numberOfSimulcastStreams <= 1 &&
53 codec.width * codec.height <= max_pixels;
54 }
55
56 bool SupportsTemporalBasedSwitch(const VideoCodec& codec) const {
57 return enable_temporal_based_switch &&
58 SimulcastUtility::NumberOfTemporalLayers(codec, 0) != 1;
59 }
60
61 bool enable_temporal_based_switch = false;
62 bool enable_resolution_based_switch = false;
63 int min_pixels = 320 * 180;
64 int max_pixels = 320 * 240;
65};
66
67const char kVp8ForceFallbackEncoderFieldTrial[] =
68 "WebRTC-VP8-Forced-Fallback-Encoder-v2";
69
70absl::optional<ForcedFallbackParams> ParseFallbackParamsFromFieldTrials(
71 const VideoEncoder& main_encoder) {
72 const std::string field_trial =
73 webrtc::field_trial::FindFullName(kVp8ForceFallbackEncoderFieldTrial);
74 if (!absl::StartsWith(field_trial, "Enabled")) {
75 return absl::nullopt;
76 }
77
78 int max_pixels_lower_bound =
79 main_encoder.GetEncoderInfo().scaling_settings.min_pixels_per_frame - 1;
80
81 ForcedFallbackParams params;
82 params.enable_resolution_based_switch = true;
83
84 int min_bps = 0;
85 if (sscanf(field_trial.c_str(), "Enabled-%d,%d,%d", &params.min_pixels,
86 &params.max_pixels, &min_bps) != 3) {
87 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
88 << "Invalid number of forced fallback parameters provided.";
89 return absl::nullopt;
90 } else if (params.min_pixels <= 0 ||
91 params.max_pixels < max_pixels_lower_bound ||
92 params.max_pixels < params.min_pixels || min_bps <= 0) {
93 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Invalid forced fallback parameter value provided.";
94 return absl::nullopt;
95 }
96
97 return params;
98}
99
100absl::optional<ForcedFallbackParams> GetForcedFallbackParams(
101 bool prefer_temporal_support,
102 const VideoEncoder& main_encoder) {
103 absl::optional<ForcedFallbackParams> params =
104 ParseFallbackParamsFromFieldTrials(main_encoder);
105 if (prefer_temporal_support) {
106 if (!params.has_value()) {
107 params.emplace();
108 }
109 params->enable_temporal_based_switch = prefer_temporal_support;
110 }
111 return params;
112}
113
114class VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper final : public VideoEncoder {
115 public:
116 VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper(
117 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> sw_encoder,
118 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> hw_encoder,
119 bool prefer_temporal_support);
120 ~VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper() override;
121
122 void SetFecControllerOverride(
123 FecControllerOverride* fec_controller_override) override;
124
125 int32_t InitEncode(const VideoCodec* codec_settings,
126 const VideoEncoder::Settings& settings) override;
127
128 int32_t RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(
129 EncodedImageCallback* callback) override;
130
131 int32_t Release() override;
132
133 int32_t Encode(const VideoFrame& frame,
134 const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frame_types) override;
135
136 void OnPacketLossRateUpdate(float packet_loss_rate) override;
137
138 void OnRttUpdate(int64_t rtt_ms) override;
139
140 void OnLossNotification(const LossNotification& loss_notification) override;
141
142 void SetRates(const RateControlParameters& parameters) override;
143
144 EncoderInfo GetEncoderInfo() const override;
145
146 private:
147 bool InitFallbackEncoder(bool is_forced);
148 bool TryInitForcedFallbackEncoder();
149 bool IsFallbackActive() const;
150
151 VideoEncoder* current_encoder() {
152 switch (encoder_state_) {
153 case EncoderState::kUninitialized:
154 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING)
155 << "Trying to access encoder in uninitialized fallback wrapper.";
156 // Return main encoder to preserve previous behavior.
157 ABSL_FALLTHROUGH_INTENDED;
158 case EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed:
159 return encoder_.get();
160 case EncoderState::kFallbackDueToFailure:
161 case EncoderState::kForcedFallback:
162 return fallback_encoder_.get();
163 }
164 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
165 }
166
167 // Updates encoder with last observed parameters, such as callbacks, rates,
168 // etc.
169 void PrimeEncoder(VideoEncoder* encoder) const;
170
171 // Settings used in the last InitEncode call and used if a dynamic fallback to
172 // software is required.
173 VideoCodec codec_settings_;
174 absl::optional<VideoEncoder::Settings> encoder_settings_;
175
176 // The last rate control settings, if set.
177 absl::optional<RateControlParameters> rate_control_parameters_;
178
179 // The last channel parameters set.
180 absl::optional<float> packet_loss_;
181 absl::optional<int64_t> rtt_;
182 FecControllerOverride* fec_controller_override_;
183 absl::optional<LossNotification> loss_notification_;
184
185 enum class EncoderState {
186 kUninitialized,
187 kMainEncoderUsed,
188 kFallbackDueToFailure,
189 kForcedFallback
190 };
191
192 EncoderState encoder_state_;
193 const std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> encoder_;
194 const std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> fallback_encoder_;
195
196 EncodedImageCallback* callback_;
197
198 const absl::optional<ForcedFallbackParams> fallback_params_;
199 int32_t EncodeWithMainEncoder(const VideoFrame& frame,
200 const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frame_types);
201};
202
203VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper(
204 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> sw_encoder,
205 std::unique_ptr<webrtc::VideoEncoder> hw_encoder,
206 bool prefer_temporal_support)
207 : fec_controller_override_(nullptr),
208 encoder_state_(EncoderState::kUninitialized),
209 encoder_(std::move(hw_encoder)),
210 fallback_encoder_(std::move(sw_encoder)),
211 callback_(nullptr),
212 fallback_params_(
213 GetForcedFallbackParams(prefer_temporal_support, *encoder_)) {
214 RTC_DCHECK(fallback_encoder_);
215}
216
217VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::~VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper() =
218 default;
219
220void VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::PrimeEncoder(
221 VideoEncoder* encoder) const {
222 RTC_DCHECK(encoder);
223 // Replay callback, rates, and channel parameters.
224 if (callback_) {
225 encoder->RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(callback_);
226 }
227 if (rate_control_parameters_) {
228 encoder->SetRates(*rate_control_parameters_);
229 }
230 if (rtt_.has_value()) {
231 encoder->OnRttUpdate(rtt_.value());
232 }
233 if (packet_loss_.has_value()) {
234 encoder->OnPacketLossRateUpdate(packet_loss_.value());
235 }
236 if (fec_controller_override_) {
237 encoder->SetFecControllerOverride(fec_controller_override_);
238 }
239 if (loss_notification_.has_value()) {
240 encoder->OnLossNotification(loss_notification_.value());
241 }
242}
243
244bool VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::InitFallbackEncoder(bool is_forced) {
245 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Encoder falling back to software encoding.";
246
247 RTC_DCHECK(encoder_settings_.has_value());
248 const int ret = fallback_encoder_->InitEncode(&codec_settings_,
249 encoder_settings_.value());
250
251 if (ret != WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
252 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to initialize software-encoder fallback.";
253 fallback_encoder_->Release();
254 return false;
255 }
256
257 if (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed) {
258 // Since we're switching to the fallback encoder, Release the real encoder.
259 // It may be re-initialized via InitEncode later, and it will continue to
260 // get Set calls for rates and channel parameters in the meantime.
261 encoder_->Release();
262 }
263
264 if (is_forced) {
265 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kForcedFallback;
266 } else {
267 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kFallbackDueToFailure;
268 }
269
270 return true;
271}
272
273void VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::SetFecControllerOverride(
274 FecControllerOverride* fec_controller_override) {
275 // It is important that only one of those would ever interact with the
276 // |fec_controller_override| at a given time. This is the responsibility
277 // of |this| to maintain.
278
279 fec_controller_override_ = fec_controller_override;
280 current_encoder()->SetFecControllerOverride(fec_controller_override);
281}
282
283int32_t VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::InitEncode(
284 const VideoCodec* codec_settings,
285 const VideoEncoder::Settings& settings) {
286 // Store settings, in case we need to dynamically switch to the fallback
287 // encoder after a failed Encode call.
288 codec_settings_ = *codec_settings;
289 encoder_settings_ = settings;
290 // Clear stored rate/channel parameters.
291 rate_control_parameters_ = absl::nullopt;
292
293 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(encoder_state_, EncoderState::kUninitialized)
294 << "InitEncode() should never be called on an active instance!";
295
296 // Try to init forced software codec if it should be used.
297 if (TryInitForcedFallbackEncoder()) {
298 PrimeEncoder(current_encoder());
299 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
300 }
301
302 int32_t ret = encoder_->InitEncode(codec_settings, settings);
303 if (ret == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
304 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed;
305 PrimeEncoder(current_encoder());
306 return ret;
307 }
308
309 // Try to instantiate software codec.
310 if (InitFallbackEncoder(/*is_forced=*/false)) {
311 PrimeEncoder(current_encoder());
312 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
313 }
314
315 // Software encoder failed too, use original return code.
316 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kUninitialized;
317 return ret;
318}
319
320int32_t VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(
321 EncodedImageCallback* callback) {
322 callback_ = callback;
323 return current_encoder()->RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(callback);
324}
325
326int32_t VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::Release() {
327 if (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kUninitialized) {
328 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
329 }
330 int32_t ret = current_encoder()->Release();
331 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kUninitialized;
332 return ret;
333}
334
335int32_t VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::Encode(
336 const VideoFrame& frame,
337 const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frame_types) {
338 switch (encoder_state_) {
339 case EncoderState::kUninitialized:
340 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERROR;
341 case EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed: {
342 return EncodeWithMainEncoder(frame, frame_types);
343 }
344 case EncoderState::kFallbackDueToFailure:
345 case EncoderState::kForcedFallback:
346 return fallback_encoder_->Encode(frame, frame_types);
347 }
348 RTC_CHECK_NOTREACHED();
349}
350
351int32_t VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::EncodeWithMainEncoder(
352 const VideoFrame& frame,
353 const std::vector<VideoFrameType>* frame_types) {
354 int32_t ret = encoder_->Encode(frame, frame_types);
355 // If requested, try a software fallback.
356 bool fallback_requested = (ret == WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_FALLBACK_SOFTWARE);
357 if (fallback_requested && InitFallbackEncoder(/*is_forced=*/false)) {
358 // Start using the fallback with this frame.
359 PrimeEncoder(current_encoder());
360 if (frame.video_frame_buffer()->type() == VideoFrameBuffer::Type::kNative &&
361 fallback_encoder_->GetEncoderInfo().supports_native_handle) {
362 return fallback_encoder_->Encode(frame, frame_types);
363 } else {
364 RTC_LOG(INFO) << "Fallback encoder does not support native handle - "
365 "converting frame to I420";
366 rtc::scoped_refptr<I420BufferInterface> src_buffer =
367 frame.video_frame_buffer()->ToI420();
368 if (!src_buffer) {
369 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to convert from to I420";
370 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ENCODER_FAILURE;
371 }
372 rtc::scoped_refptr<VideoFrameBuffer> dst_buffer =
373 src_buffer->Scale(codec_settings_.width, codec_settings_.height);
374 if (!dst_buffer) {
375 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to scale video frame.";
376 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ENCODER_FAILURE;
377 }
378 VideoFrame scaled_frame = frame;
379 scaled_frame.set_video_frame_buffer(dst_buffer);
380 scaled_frame.set_update_rect(VideoFrame::UpdateRect{
381 0, 0, scaled_frame.width(), scaled_frame.height()});
382 return fallback_encoder_->Encode(scaled_frame, frame_types);
383 }
384 }
385 // Fallback encoder failed too, return original error code.
386 return ret;
387}

411
412VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::GetEncoderInfo()
413 const {
414 EncoderInfo fallback_encoder_info = fallback_encoder_->GetEncoderInfo();
415 EncoderInfo default_encoder_info = encoder_->GetEncoderInfo();
416
417 EncoderInfo info =
418 IsFallbackActive() ? fallback_encoder_info : default_encoder_info;
419
420 if (fallback_params_.has_value()) {
421 const auto settings = (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kForcedFallback)
422 ? fallback_encoder_info.scaling_settings
423 : default_encoder_info.scaling_settings;
424 info.scaling_settings =
425 settings.thresholds
426 ? VideoEncoder::ScalingSettings(settings.thresholds->low,
427 settings.thresholds->high,
428 fallback_params_->min_pixels)
429 : VideoEncoder::ScalingSettings::kOff;
430 } else {
431 info.scaling_settings = default_encoder_info.scaling_settings;
432 }
433
434 return info;
435}
436
437bool VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::IsFallbackActive() const {
438 return encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kForcedFallback ||
439 encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kFallbackDueToFailure;
440}
441
442bool VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper::TryInitForcedFallbackEncoder() {
443 if (!fallback_params_) {
444 return false;
445 }
446
447 RTC_DCHECK_EQ(encoder_state_, EncoderState::kUninitialized);
448
449 if (fallback_params_->SupportsResolutionBasedSwitch(codec_settings_)) {
450 // Settings valid, try to instantiate software codec.
451 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "Request forced SW encoder fallback: "
452 << codec_settings_.width << "x" << codec_settings_.height;
453 return InitFallbackEncoder(/*is_forced=*/true);
454 }
455
456 if (fallback_params_->SupportsTemporalBasedSwitch(codec_settings_)) {
457 // First init main encoder to see if that supports temporal layers.
458 if (encoder_->InitEncode(&codec_settings_, encoder_settings_.value()) ==
459 WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
460 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed;
461 }
462
463 if (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed &&
464 encoder_->GetEncoderInfo().fps_allocation[0].size() != 1) {
465 // Primary encoder already supports temporal layers, use that instead.
466 return true;
467 }
468
469 // Try to initialize fallback and check if it supports temporal layers.
470 if (fallback_encoder_->InitEncode(&codec_settings_,
471 encoder_settings_.value()) ==
472 WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK) {
473 if (fallback_encoder_->GetEncoderInfo().fps_allocation[0].size() != 1) {
474 // Fallback encoder available and supports temporal layers, use it!
475 if (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed) {
476 // Main encoder initialized but does not support temporal layers,
477 // release it again.
478 encoder_->Release();
479 }
480 encoder_state_ = EncoderState::kForcedFallback;
481 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
482 << "Forced switch to SW encoder due to temporal support.";
483 return true;
484 } else {
485 // Fallback encoder intialization succeeded, but it does not support
486 // temporal layers either - release it.
487 fallback_encoder_->Release();
488 }
489 }
490
491 if (encoder_state_ == EncoderState::kMainEncoderUsed) {
492 // Main encoder already initialized - make use of it.
493 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
494 << "Cannot fall back for temporal support since fallback that "
495 "supports is not available. Using main encoder instead.";
496 return true;
497 }
498 }
499
500 // Neither forced fallback mode supported.
501 return false;
502}

506std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> CreateVideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper(
507 std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> sw_fallback_encoder,
508 std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> hw_encoder,
509 bool prefer_temporal_support) {
510 return std::make_unique<VideoEncoderSoftwareFallbackWrapper>(
511 std::move(sw_fallback_encoder), std::move(hw_encoder),
512 prefer_temporal_support);
513}
